  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/753",
  "title": "[slider/priceRange]: Allow changing the attribute filtered programmatically",
  "body": "Imagine I have a list of items to sell, and for each item I have their price stored in various currencies (euro, dollar, yen, etc). In my UI, I only want to display prices in the selected currency, but still allow users to swap displayed currency (through a dropdown menu) if they need to.\n\nI also want to let them filter the results through a slider/priceRange widget.\n\nA naive implementation would be to add three widgets, one for each currency, and add a bit of logic to hide/show them based on the currently selected currency. This will unfortunatly yield bad results: if I set a range in euros, then switch to dollars, then the range in dollar will not be correctly set. And worse, I now have no way to change or revert the range in euros.\n\nI see various ways to fix this issue:\n- Exposing a `.changeAttribute()` method on the widget itself that would allow keeping the same widget, but changing its targeted attribute\n- Allowing to `.removeWidget()` the same way we `.addWidget()` on the instantsearch instance directly and letting the user destroying the previous dollar slider and adding a euro slider instead.\n\nWhat do you think might be the best way? Or is there a more obvious solution I did not see?\n",
